‚çù --- Link.Create ---
‚çù Test that Link.Create uses the user config
 3 ‚éïNDELETE Retry‚ä¢folder
 3 ‚éïMKDIR Retry‚ä¢folder
 ‚éïEX name

 z‚ÜêLinkCreate name folder
 assert'''ns''‚â°(GetLink name).watch' ‚çù Check that user config was used
 ns‚Üê‚çéname
 ns.‚éïFX'foo' '2+2' ‚çù Little foo
 ns.‚éïFX'FOO' '3+3' ‚çù Big foo
 1 ns.‚éïSTOP'FOO'   ‚çù Check that Link.Add will register existing stops
 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Add name‚àò,¬®'.foo' '.FOO'
 files‚Üê2‚äÉ¬®‚éïNPARTS‚äÉ‚éïNINFO‚çÝ1‚ä¢folder,'/*'
 assert'''.linkconfig'' ''foo-0'' ''FOO-7'' ‚â°‚ç•{‚çµ[‚çã‚çµ]} files'
 link‚ÜêGetLink name
 assert'(,‚äÇ''FOO'')‚â°link.flagged'
 assert'(,‚äÇ,1)‚â°link.flags.Stop'

‚çù Test setting and clearing Stops
 link‚ÜêGetLink name
 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Expunge name,'.FOO'           ‚çù Should clear stops
 assert'0=‚â¢link.flagged'
 config‚Üêgetj5 folder,'/.linkconfig'
 assert'0=config.‚éïNC ''SourceFlags'''
 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Stop(fn‚Üêname,'.foo')(1 2 3) ‚çù Set on foo
 assert'(,1)‚â°‚éïSTOP ''',fn,''''
 assert'(,‚äÇ''foo'')‚â°link.flagged'
 assert'(,1)‚â°link.flags[1].Stop'
 config‚Üêgetj5 folder,'/.linkconfig'
 assert'(''caseCode'' ''recordFlags'' ''watch'')‚â°config.Settings.‚éïNL -2'
 assert'''ns'' 1‚â°config.Settings.(watch caseCode)' ‚çù Check that settings ended up in the directory config
 assert'1‚â°‚â¢config.SourceFlags'
 assert'(,1)‚â°config.SourceFlags[1].Stop'
 assert'''foo''‚â°config.SourceFlags[1].Name'
 assert'(name,''.foo 1'')‚â°‚éïSE.Link.Stop name,''.foo'''  ‚çù This will fail

 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Stop(name,'.foo')‚ç¨
 assert'‚ç¨‚â°‚éïSTOP ''',name,'.foo'''
 config‚Üêgetj5 folder,'/.linkconfig'
 assert'0=‚éïNC ''config.SourceFlags'''

 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Break name
 ‚éïEX name

‚çù Test that explicit settings override any configuration
 z‚Üê'(watch:''both'')'LinkCreate name folder
 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Configure name'fastLoad:1'
 assert'''both''‚â°(GetLink name).watch' ‚çù Explicit setting overrides config
 config‚Üêgetj5 folder,'/.linkconfig'
 assert'''ns'' 1‚â°config.Settings.(watch fastLoad)' ‚çù Directory setting should NOT be changed

 ‚çù Now set up a trace and check that it is restored on re-link
 here‚Üê‚çï‚éïTHIS                   ‚çù Do not remove the format or here will not be in scope
 ‚éïCS name                      ‚çù Check that it also works with relative names
 z‚Üê‚éïSE.UCMD'Link.Trace foo 1' ‚çù Call Trace via UCMD from inside the ns
 ‚éïCS here
 link‚ÜêGetLink name
 assert'(,‚äÇ''foo'')‚â°link.flagged'
 assert'(,1)‚â°link.flags[1].Trace'
 assert'(,1)‚â°‚éïTRACE fn'
 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Break name

‚çù /// Make a test which verifies that user config does not pollute
‚çù a directory which has default settings for someting that user config sets
‚çù z‚ÜêLinkCreate name folder

‚çù Test that folder config is used if user config says nothing

 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Configure'*' 'watch:' 'caseCode:' 'recordFlags:' ‚çù Clear user config settings
 assert'‚àß/1‚àä¬®''watch:ns'' ''caseCode:1'' ''recordFlags:1''‚ç∑¬®‚äÇz'
 assert'0=‚éïNEXISTS ‚éïSE.Link.USERCONFIGFILE' ‚çù No settings

 z‚ÜêLinkCreate name folder
 assert'''ns''‚â°(GetLink name).watch' ‚çù used folder config
 assert'(,1)‚â°‚éïTRACE name,''.foo'''   ‚çù has that trace been restored?
 z‚Üê(‚äÇ'foo' '22+22')QNPUT folder,'/foo-0.aplf'
 assert'(,1)‚â°‚éïTRACE name,''.foo'''   ‚çù has that trace been restored after re-fix?
 z‚Üê‚éïSE.Link.Break name
 ‚éïEX name

